{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01CPXh3xLBk15tgk13ecU6dw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the issue. The probes have been misconfigured:\n\nCurrent settings:\n- **livenessProbe:**\n  - `initialDelaySeconds: 15` (very short - MongoDB with auth needs more time to start)\n  - `timeoutSeconds: 1` (very short - mongosh can take longer than 1s)\n  - `failureThreshold: 2` (very low - only 2 failures before kill)\n  - `periodSeconds: 15`\n\n- **readinessProbe:**\n  - `initialDelaySeconds: 5` (way too short - MongoDB won't be ready in 5s)\n  - `timeoutSeconds: 1` (very short)\n  - `failureThreshold: 2` (very low)\n  - `periodSeconds: 10`\n\nThe original configuration had much more generous values: 60 seconds initial delay for liveness with a 10-failure threshold, and 30 seconds for readiness with 6 failures allowed. The current settings are far too aggressive and are killing the container before MongoDB has time to properly initialize.\n\nThe core issues are that mongosh authentication takes longer than 1 second, and MongoDB with authentication and replica set configuration needs more than 5-15 seconds to start up. With such short timeouts and low failure thresholds, the pod gets terminated before it's even ready. I should restore the probes to their original, more reasonable values and also verify that MongoDB is actually running and check the pod events to understand what's happening.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2270,"cache_read_input_tokens":28322,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2270},"output_tokens":12,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4087f162-5de9-4649-af72-ef27c26d6bcd","uuid":"13c8214a-9f53-493c-b3a9-600d972a90ae","